What are Engine Mounts?
Engine mounts are critical automotive components that securely connect the engine and transmission assembly to a vehicle's chassis or frame. Typically, three or four mounts support the powertrain while simultaneously isolating engine vibrations and reducing noise transmission into the passenger cabin.

Modern engine mounts incorporate advanced technologies including:

·         Hydraulic Engine Mounts for superior vibration damping

·         Active Engine Mounts with electronically controlled vibration management

·         Advanced Rubber and Composite Materials for improved durability

·         Lightweight Aluminum Components for enhanced fuel efficiency

·         Noise, Vibration & Harshness (NVH) Optimization

·         High-strength Structural Designs for improved engine stability and crash safety

By effectively isolating engine vibrations while maintaining precise engine positioning, engine mounts significantly improve ride comfort, vehicle refinement, durability, and overall driving performance.

